HEADWORD: Periderm
<hw>Per"i*derm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The outer layer of bark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The hard outer covering of
hydroids and other marine animals; the perisarc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peridiastole</ent>⟦br⟧
